8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1291, L.D. 1930, “An Act Regarding
10 Acts of Violence Committed Against a Pregnant Woman”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §214 in subsection 1 by striking out all of paragraph B
12 (page 1, lines 7 and 8 in L.D.).
13 Amend the bill in section 1 in §214 in subsection 1 by relettering the paragraphs to read
14 alphabetically.
15 Amend the bill in section 1 in §214 by striking out all of subsection 2 (page 1, lines 10
16 and 11 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
17 '2. For purposes of the following crimes, the term "person" or "human being," when
18 referring to a victim of the crime, may include an unborn child if, at the time the criminal
19 conduct was committed, the defendant knew or had reasonable cause to believe that the
20 woman against whom the criminal conduct was committed was pregnant:
21 A. Section 201, murder;
22 B. Section 202, felony murder;
23 C. Section 203, manslaughter;
24 D. Section 207, assault, and section 207-A, domestic violence assault;
25 E. Section 208, aggravated assault, and section 208-D, domestic violence aggravated
26 assault;
27 F. Section 208-A, assault while hunting; and
28 G. Section 208-B, elevated aggravated assault, and section 208-E, domestic violence
29 elevated aggravated assault.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
