COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1291, L.D. 1930
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, clarifies that a
33 defendant may be charged with and convicted of murder, felony murder, manslaughter,
44 assault, domestic violence assault, aggravated assault, domestic violence aggravated
55 assault, assault while hunting, elevated aggravated assault and domestic violence elevated
66 aggravated assault if the victim of the crime is an unborn child and if, at the time the conduct
77 was committed, the defendant knew or had reasonable cause to believe that the woman
88 against whom the defendant's criminal conduct was committed was pregnant.
99 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1100 (See attached)
